{# Reusable rendering of the `context` dict — used by both V2 (text) and V3
   (image) prompts. The dict is open-shaped: keys like `audience`, `weather`,
   `time_of_day`, `loudness`, anything the client wants to send. We dump every
   key/value pair so the model sees the full payload; `| tojson` keeps nested
   dicts/lists readable instead of falling back to Python repr.

   Callers MUST pass `context=` (possibly `None` or `{}`) — StrictUndefined
   otherwise crashes the render. #}
{%- if context %}
{%- for k, v in context.items() %}
- {{ k }}: {{ v | tojson }}
{%- endfor %}
{%- else %}
(no context provided)
{%- endif %}
